-- Italy Should Use Gains in Evasion Push to Cut Tax, Employers Say
-- B y   F r a n c e s c a   C i n e l l i
-- 2012-03-17T14:03:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-17/italy-should-use-gains-in-evasion-push-to-cut-tax-employers-say.html
Italy should use revenue it earns
from a crackdown on  tax evasion  to cut the burden on those who
do stick to the rules, a lobby for the nation’s employers said.  Italy also needs changes in its labor market to increase
productivity and employment, and the lobby is ready to sign up
for such government action “if it’s real and radical,”  Emma Marcegaglia , head of Confindustria, told a conference in Milan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
